💰 Finance Tracker Backend (MERN Stack)

A scalable backend system for managing personal finance records (income & expenses) with secure authentication and RESTful APIs.

🚀 Features
🔐 User Authentication (JWT आधारित login/signup)
👤 User Profile Management
💰 Add / Update / Delete Financial Records
📊 Track Income & Expenses
🛡️ Protected Routes with Middleware
🌐 RESTful API Design

🛠️ Tech Stack
Backend: Node.js, Express.js
Database: MongoDB (Atlas Cluster)
Authentication: JWT (JSON Web Token)
Other Tools: Mongoose, dotenv, CORS


📂 Project Structure
finance-backend/
│
├── config/
│   └── db.js              # MongoDB connection
│
├── routes/
│   ├── auth.js           # Auth routes
│   ├── users.js          # User routes
│   └── records.js        # Finance records routes
│
├── models/
│   ├── User.js
│   └── Record.js
│
├── middleware/
│   └── authMiddleware.js
│
├── .env
├── server.js
└── package.json

⚙️ Environment Variables
Create a .env file in root:

PORT=5000
MONGO_URI=your_mongodb_connection_string
JWT_SECRET=your_secret_key


▶️ Run Locally

1. Clone Repo
git clone https://github.com/rupam121/Finance_Data_Processing_Access_Control_Backend.git
cd finance-backend
2. Install Dependencies
npm install
3. Start Server
npm run dev

Server will run on:
http://localhost:5000

🔗 API Endpoints
🔐 Auth Routes

Register

POST /api/auth/register
{
  "name": "Rupam Giri",
  "email": "rupam@gmail.com",
  "password": "123456"
}

Login

POST /api/auth/login
👤 User Routes
Get Profile
GET /api/users/profile

Headers:

Authorization: Bearer TOKEN

💰 Record Routes
Add Record
POST /api/records
Get All Records
GET /api/records

Update Record
PUT /api/records/:id
Delete Record
DELETE /api/records/:id

🔒 Authentication
Uses JWT token-based authentication
Protected routes require:
Authorization: Bearer <token>

🧪 Testing
Tested using Postman

Verified:
Authentication flow
CRUD operations
Error handling

